{\textgreater}{\textgreater} The fluid is considered to be steady and laminar with constant density and viscosity throughout the fracture
- The authors present three levels of simplification to the NS equations 
1) Assume all interial forces are negligibly small compared to the forces of pressure and visocity
{\textgreater}{\textgreater} RHS of eqn 10 goes to zero (see eqn 13)
{\textgreater}{\textgreater}{\textgreater} However, in order for this assumption to be valid the Reynolds 
