{\textgreater}{\textgreater} By inserting the B.C. of u = 0 at the fracture walls and integrating one achieves an average in plane velocity vector U (see equation 16), which is later combined with the viscous and pressure forces and integrated to yield the local cubic law (LCL) (see equation 18)
